{
  "text": "(for details about how this low energy description can be obtained see [8, chapter 4] This example is, of course, too simple for our purposes. It has only one type of excitations and these particles are free. More interesting examples with more realistic particle content do exist. A particularly interesting example that is also built using spins on a lattice was proposed by Levin and Wen [CITATION_1] . They argue that their model gives rise to QED-like physics at low energies. The details of how special relativity emerges at low energies are discussed in [10] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
